main event: Two separate reports from April 1953 detail the sighting of a fast-moving, circular object resembling a small white-colored star near Detroit Lakes, Minnesota.
interesting points: The object was observed for about 15 minutes, during which it moved in circular patterns before suddenly vanishing in one report.
The sighting took place in overcast weather conditions.
One of the reports indicates that the object was observed at CRAGGY POINT, 7 miles southeast of Detroit Lakes, Minnesota.
No photographs or physical evidence were obtained during the observations.
The conclusion drawn was 'INSUFFICIENT DATA FOR EVALUATION.'
sighted object: fast-moving, circular object resembling a small white-colored star
